<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="315" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="14.[677,1218,1137,1225]" pageId="14" pageNumber="315">
ETYMOLOGY: 
<taxonomicName authority="(Latin)" baseAuthorityName="Latin" box="[806,955,1137,1159]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Bulbophyllum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="14" pageNumber="315" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="subium">
<emphasis box="[806,878,1137,1158]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="315">subium</emphasis>
(Latin)
</taxonomicName>
= moustache, referring to shape of the hairy patches on the lip (the word is used as a noun in apposition.
</paragraph>
